            <article data-uuid="294466fe501a4f3489836383824c91eb">
                <h4 data-uuid="75e824ca808b41818054950b2ca55731">Main Idea</h4>
                <p class="main-idea" data-uuid="10dd013a7b9e46529e5f8a02a3557f3e">Following the war, minority groups organized to demand their civil rights.</p>
                <h2 data-uuid="a386bf4ca884427c8299c31b8cd5b4a9">Minority Rights</h2>
                <div class="yellow-star-yellow-bar" data-uuid="934314d0e70a43b3b1176997b7f2d938"></div>
            </article>
        </section>
        <p data-uuid="3d5493318adc4d2e849b53d5343e2922" class="">During World War I, large numbers of African Americans began leaving the South to take jobs in northern factories. This movement, or migration, continued during the economic boom of the 1920s. It was called the <dfn title="Great Migration">Great Migration</dfn>. While African Americans found jobs in the North, they did not escape racism. During the Great Migration, northern cities, such as New York City, grew.</p>
