        <h3 data-uuid="6888ebd4e81d4a30a912714db9e2fb6c">Racial Tensions</h3>
        <p data-uuid="1a1ed6f04528452eb599e8377f507397">The economic recession that followed the war led to increased racial tensions. Many white laborers feared the competition for jobs. Several race riots broke out. In 1919 a race riot in Chicago left 38 dead. This riot was considered the worst of the approximately 25 riots that occurred during the Red Summer of 1919. In 1921 a group of whites attacked a community of African Americans in Tulsa, Oklahoma. This resulted in the businesses and homes of the Greenwood District being destroyed. At that time, the Greenwood District was the wealthiest black community in the United States. <br />
        </p>
